message.content:
We first identify the quick assets. Quick assets usually include Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, and Accounts Receivable but exclude Inventory. Using the End_amounts:

• Cash on Hand: 4,303,451.63  
• Bank Deposits: 2,938,804.13  
• Interest Receivable: 8,592.81  
• Accounts Receivable: 1,502,354.84  

Sum the quick assets:  
4,303,451.63 + 2,938,804.13 = 7,242,255.76  
7,242,255.76 + 8,592.81 = 7,250,848.57  
7,250,848.57 + 1,502,354.84 = 8,753,203.41

Next, take the Total Current Liabilities at the end (728,279.50) as the denominator.

The Quick Ratio is then:  
Quick Ratio = (Quick Assets) / (Current Liabilities)  
= 8,753,203.41 / 728,279.50 ≈ 12.02

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Quick Ratio": "12.02"}}
